====================
GLOBAL CONTROL
====================

57. Global router order (final target)
1. `start.router`
2. `timezone.router`
3. `wizard.router`
4. `task_browser.router`
5. `event_edit.router`
6. `weekly.router` (compatibility wrapper, mandatory)
7. `callbacks.router`
8. `metrics.router` (fixed position: after callbacks.router)

58. Global non-functional requirements
1. No synchronous blocking I/O in handlers.
2. Callback p95 processing target < 300ms (excluding Telegram network latency).
3. DB operations use transactions for multi-step mutations.

59. Global migration policy
1. Schema evolves only via `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` and indexes.
2. Existing data remains backward-compatible.
3. Backup is required before phases that alter schema (Phase 5, Phase 7).

60. Global completion gate
1. All phase acceptance criteria are satisfied.
2. Full regression passes (`pytest -q`).
3. Manual QA pass per phase is documented.
4. Production rollout logs and rollback instructions are stored.

61. Current code to target UX delta (audit result)
1. Main menu currently already matches target buttons:
2. `["Напомнить", "Мои активности на неделю"]`.
3. Current weekly list sends one message per event and only button "Удалить"; target requires single browser message with edit/clone/delete per item.
4. Current wizard date entry is text-only; target requires calendar-first with quick dates and same-message month navigation.
5. Current wizard supports edit only before save; target adds edit for already saved tasks from list.
6. Current reminder callbacks do not verify ownership; target requires ownership validation for all event-id callbacks.
7. Current cancellation UX is consistent for wizard; target keeps this and extends cancel availability in browser/calendars.

62. Button convenience rules (mandatory)
1. Any inline keyboard used for navigation must include explicit cancel/close action.
2. User must be able to return to main menu from any long flow in at most 2 taps.
3. No screen may require memorizing numeric ids; all item actions are button-driven by event card.
4. After mutating action (save/edit/delete/undo/clone), bot sends explicit confirmation text and keeps user in predictable context:
5. create/edit flows -> MAIN_MENU.
6. browser actions -> browser message refresh on same page/filter.
7. close/cancel action always removes active inline controls from the current message.
